		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Acmlm, BMF, and I have all noticed that we'll occasionally get some weird scanlines while playing various older NES games, like SMB.
<br />
<br />On SMB, we'll occasionally get a scanline that has some brown junk, and it'll just be somewhere in the middle of the sky for a frame.
<br />
<br />I was also getting this issue in the horizontally-scrolling section of Kid Icarus, where as I scroll, there'll be the occasional "wrong" scanline somewhere in the screen. The weird thing is that this doesn't always happen; sometimes I'll play the game and never get this quirk, and sometimes I'll play the game and get this quirk a lot, but it's <em>always</em> in the horizontally-scrolling segments of the game.
<br />
<br />Could this be related?

		

